4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under the Alabama Jobs Act, certain projects
6 qualify for economic tax incentives awarded by the
7 Secretary of Commerce.
8 This bill would require any company receiving an
9 economic tax incentive under the Alabama Jobs Act to
10 certify that the company does not require overtime,
11 does not practice shift rotation, does not require
12 weekend work, provides emergency leave, guarantees a
13 full work week, does not require off-the-clock work,
14 and does not count the time an employee spends
15 transitioning to or from a bathroom or breakroom to
16 count toward the employee's allotted break time.
17
18
19 A BILL
20 TO BE ENTITLED
21 AN ACT
22
23 Relating to economic incentives; to add Section
24 40-18-372.1 to the Code of Alabama 1975; to prohibit companies
25 receiving certain economic tax incentives from certain
26 employment actions; and to require those companies to provide
27 certain employment protections for workers.
28 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
Page 1

BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
HB352 INTRODUCED
29 Section 1. Section 40-18-372.1 is added to the Code of
30 Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
31 §40-18-372.1
32 Notwithstanding any law to the contrary, on and after
33 January 1, 2027, the Secretary of Commerce may not find any
34 project to be a qualifying project under Section 40-18-372
35 unless the company seeking a job act incentive certifies that
36 the company, for the duration of any tax incentive received
37 under this article:
38 (1) Does not require mandatory overtime of any
39 employee;
40 (2) Does not engage in shift rotation whereby an
41 employee is asked or required to work a shift that changes
42 from one shift to another on a rotating basis;
43 (3) Does not require any employee to work weekends;
44 (4) Entitles an employee to at least 40 hours annually
45 of paid emergency leave;
46 (5) Guarantees a 40 hour work week unless an
47 unforeseeable event occurs that threatens the health, safety,
48 or welfare of the employees;
49 (6) Does not require any employee to perform tasks that
50 would reasonably be considered part of an employee's job
51 duties before or after the employee has clocked in or out or
52 outside the employee's shift; and
53 (7) Does not require an employee to use any portion of
54 his or her entitled break time to transit from the employee's
55 work station to a bathroom or breakroom.
56 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
